A class (K, \leq ) of finite \mathcal {L}-structures (closed under isomorphism) is called a smooth class if \leq is transitive, A \leq  B  \Rightarrow  A \subsetq  B, and for each A \in  K, there is a set of universal formulas \Phi _A such that:
A \leq  B  \Leftrightarrow  B \models   \Phi _A(A)
and we require that A \cong  A'  \Leftrightarrow   \Phi _A =  \Phi _{A'}

